---
description: Persist Learning Tutor queue or covered updates when a learning event, explicit study-log request, or successful assessment requires a profile write.
alwaysApply: false
---

When a learning event requires a profile write, use this persistence contract.
Prefer the stable CLI; do not edit `profile.md` directly unless the CLI is
unavailable.

## CLI (preferred)
```bash
python3 ~/.cursor/learning/cli.py want --topic "TOPIC" --note "why"
python3 ~/.cursor/learning/cli.py covered --topic "TOPIC" --level "beginner|intermediate|advanced" --note "context"
```

If `~/.cursor/learning/cli.py` is missing, tell the user to open a new chat so
`sessionStart` can install it, or use `/study-log`.

## Marker fallback (afterAgentResponse hook)
Isolated line at the end of the reply:
```
<!-- LEARNING-WANT topic="TOPIC" note="context" -->
<!-- LEARNING-LOG topic="TOPIC" level="intermediate" note="context" -->
```

## When to write
- `concept_gap` or “add to queue / study later” → `want`
- Explicit user request or `/study-log` → `want` or `covered` as requested
- Successful `study-probe` evidence → `covered` (gaps stay or become `want`)

## When not to write
- `repo_local` answers, purely operational replies, or plugin meta
- Do **not** infer `covered` merely because a concept was explained in chat

## Required feedback
After a successful write: one line `Saved to profile: …` or `Saved to queue: …`.
If the CLI replies “Already in queue” / “Ignored”, do not insist.
